  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Manager for Employment Agency",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Manage full time and part-time sales &amp; marketing executives to promote our business to customers</li>\n  <li>Maintain effective liaison and coordination with overseas sources of supply, especially foreign employment agencies in Myanmar or Indonesia or the Philippines</li>\n  <li>Provide client support in aligning their requirements and expectations by using strong consultation and negotiation skills</li>\n  <li>Identify and develop new customers through professional networking and various marketing channels.</li>\n  <li>Meeting and exceeding monthly sales targets.</li>\n  <li>Degree + Min 5 years related work experience</li>\n  <li>Applicants must have a Certificate of Employment Intermediaries (CEI).</li>\n  <li>Passion for sales and a strong will to succeed in the employment agency business.</li>\n  <li>Result-oriented and sales-focused.</li>\n  <li>Excellent marketing and sales skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to multi-task and perform under stress.</li>\n  <li>Enjoy working in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Good people skills and the cultural awareness to manage a diverse team of sales &amp; marketing executives</li>\n</ul>\n<p>* We expect the candidate to have adequate competence to speak one foreign language to communicate with migrant domestic workers or the company's overseas collaborators</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>* Outstanding performers can expect excellent financial rewards (good commission)</p>",
